    "remarks": {
      "sha256": "03198aafebd1d370cdab491cbea34ca10bf202c06b3cb931f1301cc6ccf9adaa",
      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A problem of Erd\\H{o}s, Hajnal, S\\'{o}s, and Szemer\\'{e}di, who could prove this is true for $\\delta>1/8$.\n\nSee also [533] and the entry in the graphs problem collection."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "49b1288627e56eeadc20ab20591087d03952409f41a205c15929f3a9f1e3aa18",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "Let $\\delta>0$. If $n$ is sufficiently large and $G$ is a graph on $n$ vertices with no $K_{2,2,2}$ and at least $\\delta n^2$ edges then $G$ contains an independent set of size $\\gg_\\delta n$."
    }
  },
